# kart.delete on a kart that exists in neither devpod nor the garage is the
# one lifecycle verb that errors on missing: code:3 kart_not_found. This
# test proves:
#   - kart.delete is registered (no method_not_found)
#   - param binding works (name required)
#   - the not_found path fires when both sides are empty
#
# The test assumes devpod, if present on PATH, reports an empty workspace
# list for a fresh $HOME — true in CI and in the devcontainer sandbox.

stdin delete.json
lakitu rpc
! stderr .
stdout '"error":'
! stdout 'method_not_found'
stdout '"code":3'
stdout '"type":"kart_not_found"'
stdout '"kart":"ghost"'

-- delete.json --
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","method":"kart.delete","params":{"name":"ghost"},"id":1}
